6.description:
The creditor filed a lawsuit to recover the debt from the debtor under a financial agricultural receipt.  Under the terms of the FAR, the creditor demanded payment of:

(1) the principal amount;
(2) penalty (at double the NBU discount rate);
(3) fine (30%);
(4) fee for use of funds (36% per annum);
(5) losses from inflation.

8.description:
Although agricultural notes did not contain references to the counter-obligation under the contract, the Supreme Court concluded that this is not explicitly required by law; specifically, it noted that:
- the absence of contract details in the agricultural note is not a ground for its nullity;
- to acquire the status of creditor under the agricultural note, it is decisive to prove the existence of contractual obligations under which the debtor issued such a note, rather than indicating the contract details in the financial agricultural note.
